## Project Overview

This project is a mini-erp focused on invoice management for devs in Brazil that works for companies offshore

## Tech Stack

- React 19+ with TypeScript
- Tailwind CSS v4
- Bun
- Biome

## Warnings

- do not run bun scripts unless told to
- do not run the integrated browser unless told to
- do not create/manipulate migrations unless told to

## Code Quality & Rules

- Filenames must be written in PascalCase, for example DataTable.tsx
- Folders must be written in kebab-case, for example data-table
- Use consts with arrow functions instead of regular functions
- Try to put dedicated types into a types.ts file when possible
- Do not add comments to code unless explicitly asked or very needed (e.g., complex business logic, non-obvious workarounds)
- Use semantic HTML elements
- Do not use `export * ...` or `import * ...`
- Do not use default exports

## React Component Rules

- Only put one React component per file, except for small helper
  components
- Always use named exports for components, types, and utilities
- Do not use forwardRef for components that need ref forwarding. Use React 19 approach for ref as a prop.

